Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update package index and install Python tooling
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3-pip
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the verification test-suite
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial workspace expected by the exercise’s test harness
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create the dedicated home sub-directory
    mkdir -p /home/user
    # Make it writable by any unprivileged runtime user
    chmod 0777 /home/user

    # Create the firewall manifest with exactly one newline-terminated line
    printf "# ETL Pipeline Firewall Rules\n" > /home/user/etl_firewall_rules.conf
    # Ensure the file is writable by any user so the student can append to it
    chmod 0666 /home/user/etl_firewall_rules.conf

    # Do NOT create /home/user/etl_firewall_apply.log; the student must make it
    :

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author firewall-task-setup
    Description "Container for firewall manifest task – includes initial state and pytest"

%help
This Apptainer image provides the initial filesystem state for the
“firewall manifest” exercise.  
It already contains:
  • /home/user/etl_firewall_rules.conf  (one specific line, writable)
Pytest is installed so the evaluation harness can run.